,NULL,0,'','2011-12-09 19:28:47',NULL,NULL,'that is correct',NULL,'@'),(198,'A',186,3,1,3,NULL,0,NULL,2,NULL,1915616439,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','2011-12-09 19:32:22',NULL,NULL,'As some one else has asked, if your system is web based, typically there is no need to install.  For maintenance, the other answer is right.  In fact, we can use a change-order table, very similar to the test plan, to manage the maintenance.',NULL,'@'),(199,'C',196,3,1,3,NULL,0,NULL,35,NULL,1195135250,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','2011-12-09 20:09:26',NULL,NULL,'I didn\'t receive an email.',NULL,'@'),(200,'C',194,3,1,3,NULL,0,NULL,53,NULL,1813077573,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','2011-12-09 21:10:27',NULL,NULL,'That is a brilliant and hilarious!',NULL,NULL),(201,'A',185,3,1,3,NULL,0,NULL,2,NULL,1990851153,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','2011-12-10 07:27:55',NULL,NULL,'I just resent the e-mail',NULL,'@'),(202,'Q',NULL,3,1,3,NULL,1,NULL,23,NULL,1204253369,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,2530493116,6,1.22658e+10,0,'','2011-12-10 11:52:05',NULL,'Updated Docs Question','Do we have to included the previous revisions when we turn in our documents or do you only want the final version?','','@'),(203,'Q',NULL,3,1,3,NULL,1,NULL,6,NULL,1204253526,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,2184306655,12,1.22727e+10,0,'','2011-12-11 00:27:10',NULL,'What is required for the Source Code?','How should the source code be labeled and if we have used imported libraries that we did not write, do we still need to include them in the Source Code document?','','@'),(204,'A',203,3,1,3,NULL,0,NULL,2,NULL,3538263616,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','2011-12-11 00:36:21',NULL,NULL,'no need to include libraries.  Just include the Java source, or PHP source you wrote.',NULL,'@'),(205,'A',202,3,1,3,NULL,0,NULL,2,NULL,3538263616,2,3538263616,1,0,1,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','2011-12-11 00:37:45','2011-12-11 00:38:18',NULL,'No need to include previous versions.  Just include the final version, but please make sure you faithfully recorded in the revision histories what you did in each update.',NULL,'@'),(206,'Q',NULL,3,1,3,NULL,1,NULL,53,NULL,1813077573,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,2530476913,11,1.22958e+10,0,'html','2011-12-12 07:20:10',NULL,'Symbol ** in formal verification','<p>\n	The following line is from an example slide in our formal verification techniques:</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<b style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: medium;\">{output = input1 ** input2}</b></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	What do the double asterisks ** signify?</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>','','@'),(207,'A',206,3,1,3,NULL,0,NULL,5,NULL,402898008,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','2011-12-12 10:56:42',NULL,NULL,'I think it\'s exponentiation, so input1 ** input 2 == input1^input2.',NULL,'@'),(208,'Q',NULL,3,1,3,NULL,3,NULL,49,NULL,2530487429,NULL,NULL,3,0,3,1248816143,72,1.2403e+10,0,'','2011-12-12 12:49:21',NULL,'What time is our final?','Im rather concerned. Thank you.','',NULL),(209,'A',208,3,1,3,NULL,0,NULL,23,NULL,1204253369,NULL,NULL,3,6,-3,NULL,0,NULL,1,'html','2011-12-12 12:52:01',NULL,NULL,'<p>\n	4PM today as noted by the calendar:&nbsp;<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.cs.pitt.edu/~chang/153/calendar\">http://www.cs.pitt.edu/~chang/153/calendar</a></p>',NULL,NULL),(210,'A',208,3,1,3,NULL,0,NULL,46,NULL,2530493116,NULL,NULL,5,1,4,NULL,0,NULL,2,'','2011-12-12 12:57:18',NULL,NULL,'I think its 8am on Saturday',NULL,'@'),(211,'Q',NULL,3,1,3,NULL,1,NULL,47,NULL,2530484720,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,2530476922,9,1.22986e+10,0,'','2011-12-12 13:00:42',NULL,'No quiz three grade in grade vector, when will we receive grade?','','','@'),(212,'C',210,3,1,3,NULL,0,NULL,66,NULL,2530487766,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','2011-12-12 13:06:48',NULL,NULL,'also it\'s in the basement of the cathedral',NULL,'@'),(213,'C',209,3,1,3,NULL,0,NULL,8,NULL,2184305747,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,NULL,0,NULL,1,'','2011-12-12 13:09:34',NULL,NULL,'Wow cannot believe the right answer is being downvoted....',NULL,NULL),(214,'C',210,3,1,3,NULL,0,NUL